document_data.Abilities:
The Rotting Man was incapable of dying to disease, gaining strength from them instead.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|171|17}}{{cite book/Lady of Poison|204|20}} He also knew a number of curse words capable of binding his own soul, which he used almost casually, most likely spoken in the [[Dark Speech]].{{cite book/Lady of Poison|166|17}}

When in combat, he could lauch overwhelming waves of rot; their exact effects were unknown, but they could be blocked by other divine beings, such as the aspect Araluen.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|282|30}} On those occassions he deigned engage personally, he employed shapeshifting as the capstone of his strategy.

He had also performed rites to capture the power of the aspect of Lurue{{cite book/Lady of Poison|126|13}}
